{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Meringue","content":["Preheat oven to 100°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh caster sugar into it. Set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites into mixing bowl and beat <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>, <strong> without measuring cup<\/strong>, or until soft peaks form.","Beat <nobr>3-5 min\/37°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, gradually adding reserved caster sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid one spoonful at a time, until sugar dissolves and stiff peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk. <\/strong> ","Transfer meringue mixture onto prepared baking tray, spreading out to a 2 cm thickness. Bake for 80 minutes (100°C). Turn off oven and leave meringue in oven to cool for 1 hour. Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."]},{"title":"Passionfruit curd","content":["Strain passionfruit pulp through a fine-mesh sieve into a jug. Reserve any remaining pulp and seeds."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place passionfruit juice, orange juice, sugar, butter and eggs into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>8 min\/80°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Check to see if mixture has reached setting point by inserting a spoon into curd. Curd should coat the back of the spoon in a thick layer. If curd is not set, cook for a further <nobr>2-3 min\/80°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, or until thickened. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Transfer curd into a sealable jar or container and set aside to cool to room temperature, then place into refrigerator until cold. Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":[" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>30-40 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>, or until soft peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","To assemble, dollop  2-3 teaspoons passionfruit curd and 2-3 teaspoons whipped cream onto 6 serving plates in any pattern you like. Break meringue into shards and decorate each plate with 1-2 meringue pieces. Garnish with orange segments, mint leaves and reserved passionfruit pulp and seeds. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Meringue","content":["100 g caster sugar","3 egg whites"]},{"title":"Passionfruit curd","content":["80 g passionfruit pulp","40 g orange juice (approx. 1 orange)","50 g caster sugar","80 g unsalted butter, softened","3 eggs"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["200 g pouring (whipping) cream","2 oranges, segmented","10 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only"]}],"id":"r109140","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-t9JkxFI5Ro0\/XZWdBNSmo3I\/AAAAAAAAeiE\/cWPHX83zEM0w9MhEp-cSwXvoTUKGm2a3ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_BUMGLurV_8cH50v9.png","title":"Orange and passionfruit Eton mess","publishedAt":"2016-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.1 g","fat":"21.8 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"30.8 g","calories":"1433 kJ \/ 341 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, ceramic or glass bowl, fine mesh sieve, jug, sealable storage jar or container, 6 serving plates, oven, refrigerator","basicInfo":["easy","40m","2h 50m","6 portions"]}